  <entry>
    <title>口语（测试文档）</title>
    <link href="https://li-san-huo.gitee.io/2023/08/05/%E5%8F%A3%E8%AF%AD%EF%BC%88%E6%B5%8B%E8%AF%95%E6%96%87%E6%A1%A3%EF%BC%89-1/"/>
    <id>https://li-san-huo.gitee.io/2023/08/05/%E5%8F%A3%E8%AF%AD%EF%BC%88%E6%B5%8B%E8%AF%95%E6%96%87%E6%A1%A3%EF%BC%89-1/</id>
    <published>2023-08-05T12:15:25.000Z</published>
    <updated>2023-08-10T07:28:03.589Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="雅思口语"><a href="#雅思口语" class="headerlink" title="雅思口语"></a>雅思口语</h1><h3 id="1—4月题"><a href="#1—4月题" class="headerlink" title="1—4月题"></a>1—4月题</h3><h6 id="浅浅记录一下"><a href="#浅浅记录一下" class="headerlink" title="浅浅记录一下"></a>浅浅记录一下</h6><span id="more"></span><h2 id="Hometown"><a href="#Hometown" class="headerlink" title="Hometown"></a>Hometown</h2><ol><li><p><strong>Where is your hometown?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">My hometown is in the countryside next to Zhengzhou, and it name is Xinmi.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Is it a big city or a small place?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">At present, it is only a small rural area, and many places have not been developed. However, the local government has been renovating in the past two years to develop attractions and tourism, and it will become bigger in the future</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Do you like your hometown?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Of course, my hometown has a beautiful environment, with more than 300 large and small peaks, dense vegetation, and a lot of land, mineral and plant resources. At the same time, it also has a long history and culture, and was once the hometown of the Chinese mythical figure Fuxi Nuwa.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What do you like most about your hometown?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I lik my hometown environment and slow pace little pressure, like I just said, there are a lot of mountains, water, vegetation, beautiful environment. and the mood can be well relaxed. It&#x27;s not like the very fast pace in big cities, which leads to a very tired heart.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Is there anything you dislike about it?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">There are places not to like, because it is rural, the roads are small, the facilities are relatively old, and there is no strong public transportation system. Therefore, the equipment and daily travel required for life are inconvenient</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>How long have you been living there?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Usually I only go back on important statutory holidays, because there are usually few times when I can only take holidays on statutory holidays. If the holiday time is relatively short, such as the Dragon Boat Festival, Labor Day is only 1 day, I may only go back for more than ten hours or not go back. If the holiday is longer, such as National Day, there are 3 days for the Spring Festival, I will go back for 2 days.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Do you like living there?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Yes, I loved staying there. Like I said before, the environment is good and the pressure to live there is very small. I enjoy this kind of life, it can change my mood and it doesn&#x27;t make me anxious.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Do you think you will continue living there for a long time?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I don&#x27;t think I&#x27;m going to live there for long because there are no good jobs and the wages are so low that I&#x27;m not sure if that will feed me. Downtown tends to have better jobs and more opportunities, and I need to look for work in the city. Maybe I&#x27;ll live there for a long time when I&#x27;m old, but not at the moment.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Please describe your hometown a little.</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Well, Xinmi has a long history, beautiful environment and rich resources. Its mineral and food value is very important, first of all, mineral resources mainly include coal, bauxite, limestone, silica. The geological reserves of coalfield are 5 billion tons, of which 1.65 billion tons are in the coal industry, 60 million tons of aluminum-vanadium reserves, 1 billion tons of industrial silicon reserves and 5 billion tons of limestone reserves, all of which have great industrial value. The second is grain, with a total annual grain output of 200,000 tons, mainly wheat, corn, vegetables and fruits.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What’s your hometown famous for?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">My hometown is famous for jade and grilled fish, first and foremost jade. Xinmi is a famous source of dense jade in China. It was developed and utilized in ancient times. In 1960, a large piece of jade 1.28 meters high and weighing 1.35 tons was found, which was praised by Chinese leaders. It is now listed as a national treasure and is preserved in the Shanghai Museum. New dense jade is mostly used in the production of small jade and jewelry, especially ornaments or artworks produced by green dense jade, and is deeply loved by Chinese and foreign people. The second is grilled fish, and the new secret grilled fish can make catfish that people don&#x27;t eat often or even hate to eat very delicious, and has developed to many cities.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Did you learn about the history of your hometown at school?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">To be honest, I didn&#x27;t learn the history of my hometown at school, maybe only my hometown school did. In China&#x27;s history education, it is often very famous, a major event, and of great strategic significance. Because my hometown is just a small rural village, and there are many such places and more famous and better places in China, my hometown is very ordinary and even inconspicuous in China&#x27;s history. So I didn&#x27;t learn about the history of my hometown in the history study at school.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ol><hr><h2 id="Home-and-accommodation"><a href="#Home-and-accommodation" class="headerlink" title="Home and accommodation"></a>Home and accommodation</h2><ol><li><p><strong>Do you live in a house or a flat?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I live on the 11th floor of the apartment, which is located in the south of Zhengzhou, a little bit far from the city center, more than 20 kilometers. Because the price there will be a little cheaper.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Can you describe the place where you live?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I live in a small place, 90 square meters. The four people who lived me, my parents and my sister were a bit tight. There are three bedrooms, two large and a small one. Two washrooms, a kitchen, a living room and a balcony. There is no separate dining room, and because it is connected to the living room, there is only one dining table.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>How long have you lived there?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I moved there in high school and it&#x27;s been 5 years now</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Please describe the room you live in</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">My room was that little bedroom so there were very few things. There is only one bed, a wardrobe and desk attached to the wall. Next to the bed is a window with a small air conditioner on it. Because the room is small, even a small air conditioner can keep the room at a comfortable temperature all the time.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What part of your home do you like the most</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I like the living room in my home the most. First because it&#x27;s the biggest space in my home, then there&#x27;s a big soft sofa that&#x27;s comfortable to lie on, and finally it&#x27;s in the middle of the home and it&#x27;s also very light.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Who do you live with?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">There were four people living in the family, me, my parents and my sister. However, I live in a room by myself, and I like to have my own private space, without feeling very depressed and tired</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What room does your family spend most of the time in?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I think the restaurant should spend the most time together, because usually my parents have to go to work and my sister and I go to school. So there is no one at home most of the day. I came back late in the evening and slept in my room most of the time. Therefore, I usually spend it in the restaurant only at breakfast</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What do you usually do in your flat?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I usually eat and sleep in the apartment because I have to go to school, most of the time at school. Sometimes when I have a holiday, I play games and watch TV in the apartment.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What kinds of accommodation do you live in?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">As I stayed in an apartment, each room was almost rectangular. There are four neighbors on each floor. And the place is not big, it will be a little crowded</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Do you plan to live there for a long time?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I think not, because I may go to other cities to work and live in the future, so I will not live for a long time, maybe two years</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Do you prefer living in a house or a flat?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">If I have money, I prefer to live in a house, because the house is big, I hardly have to worry that I have a lot of things that I don&#x27;t have to put and I want to put a lot of interesting equipment. Moreover, I can decorate it to my liking.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Are the transport facilities to you home very good?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Because my house is on the edge of the city center, it is not very good, and I need to change other cars in the middle. But there is always a transport line to my house</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What kind of house or flat do you want to live in the future?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">If I have money, I would like to live in a basement, a garage and a large house with two or three floors. The basement is mainly used for parking and storing supplies, and the garage is mainly used to repair the car, because I like the car, and I like to be able to do some simple repairs and modifications by myself, so I need to have a lot of maintenance tools in the garage.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What’s your favorite room in your apartment&#x2F;house?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I think it must be my playroom. If I had a game room, I wouldn&#x27;t hesitate to put on powerful and excellent computer, virtual reality and vehicle simulator equipment. I can stay in it for a long time</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What makes you feel pleasant in your home?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I don&#x27;t spend much time at home, only at home when I go to bed at night, and most of the time at school. If anything, it must be a holiday at home, a good night&#x27;s sleep, and a leisurely life will be happy at home</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>What’s the difference between where you are living now and where you have lived in the past?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Where I used to live, the house was older, there were fewer people, the floors were not high, there were 6 floors in total, and there was no elevator. Now there are many people living in the place, but it is also more noisy, and the floors are very high, with 32 floors. There are also many restaurants in the surrounding area</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Do you think it is important to live in a comfortable environment?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Yes, I think it&#x27;s important. Because this has a lot to do with quality of life and happiness. A comfortable environment can greatly relieve people&#x27;s stress, make people have a better mood, reduce anxiety, depression and many mental diseases. And will be able to reduce the crime rate.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ol><hr><h2 id="Snacks"><a href="#Snacks" class="headerlink" title="Snacks"></a>Snacks</h2><ol><li><p><strong>what snacks do you like to eat?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">My favorite snacks are fried chicken, chips and soft drinks. These high-calorie foods can make me feel good and less tired.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Did you often eat snacks when you were young?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Although I would love to eat, I don&#x27;t eat it very often. Because my parents thought those were junk foods that I wouldn&#x27;t be allowed to eat, and as a child there was almost no pocket money and it was hard to buy.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>When do you usually eat snacks now?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I usually snack at night now, and I tend to be hungry at night before going to bed, and my appetite grows. At this time, eating snacks can also reduce the fatigue of the day. Imagine sitting in front of a computer or TV and eating a snack.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Do you think it is healthy for you to eat snacks?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I don&#x27;t think snacking is healthy for me, because delicious snacks are often high in sugar, salt or fat, and regular snacking can easily cause a lot of load on the body, resulting in a series of chronic diseases. Although I don&#x27;t think it&#x27;s healthy for me, in a fast-paced and high-stress big city, it&#x27;s the only legal way to reduce physical and mental fatigue, relaxation and happiness at great speed and low cost.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ol><hr><h2 id="Weather"><a href="#Weather" class="headerlink" title="Weather"></a>Weather</h2><ol><li><p><strong>what’s the weather like where you live?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Most weather is relatively stable and the changes are not as big. Generally, only in summer, like July and August, there will be a lot of rainfall, and there will be more wind when the seasons change.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Do you prefer cold or hot weather?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I prefer cool days. Because the hot weather makes me feel agitated, and in the cool weather I can wear my favorite coat.</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Do you prefer dry or wet weather?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I prefer dry weather. I feel stuffy because of the wet weather, and it&#x27;s also more likely to mold food and clothes</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>Are you in the habit of checking the weather forecast? When&#x2F;how often?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">There is no such habit. I usually only check the weather forecast when I think about it, or when I have something special the next day. Because weather forecasts are sometimes inaccurate</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p><strong>what do you think are the effects of climate change in recent years?</strong></p><figure class="highlight plaintext"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">I think the impact of climate change is more and more frequent extreme weather. The increase in average temperature caused by the greenhouse effect. This causes El Niño and La Niña to alternate repeatedly, with extreme cold and heat repeatedly</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li></ol><h1 id="尾部，继续添加中。。。"><a href="#尾部，继续添加中。。。" class="headerlink" title="尾部，继续添加中。。。"></a>尾部，继续添加中。。。</h1>]]></content>
    
    
